{"name": "clonearmy", "metadata": {"name": "cloneArmy", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["biopython", "click", "jinja2", "matplotlib", "networkx", "pandas", "pysam", "rich", "scipy", "seaborn"], "summary": "Analyze haplotypes from Illumina paired-end amplicon sequencing", "upload_time": 1732233427}, "documentation": ["# CloneArmy\n\nCloneArmy is a modern Python package for analyzing haplotypes from Illumina paired-end amplicon sequencing data. It provides a streamlined workflow for processing FASTQ files, aligning reads, and identifying sequence variants.\n\n## Features\n\n- Fast paired-end read processing using BWA-MEM\n- Quality-based filtering of bases and alignments\n- Haplotype identification and frequency analysis\n- Rich command-line interface with progress tracking\n- Comprehensive output reports\n- Multi-threading support\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install cloneArmy\n```\n\n### Requirements\n\n- Python \u2265 3.8\n- BWA (must be installed and available in PATH)\n- Samtools (must be installed and available in PATH)\n\n## Usage\n\n### Command Line Interface\n\n```bash\n# Basic usage\ncloneArmy /path/to/fastq/directory reference.fasta\n\n# With all options\ncloneArmy /path/to/fastq/directory reference.fasta \\\n    --threads 8 \\\n    --output results \\\n    --min-base-quality 20 \\\n    --min-mapping-quality 30\n```\n\n### Python API\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom clone_army.processor import AmpliconProcessor\n\n# Initialize processor\nprocessor = AmpliconProcessor(\n    reference_path=\"reference.fasta\",\n    min_base_quality=20,\n    min_mapping_quality=30\n)\n\n# Process a single sample\nresults = processor.process_sample(\n    fastq_r1=\"sample_R1.fastq.gz\",\n    fastq_r2=\"sample_R2.fastq.gz\",\n    output_dir=\"results\",\n    threads=4\n)\n\n# Results are returned as a pandas DataFrame\nprint(results)\n```\n\n## Output\n\nFor each sample, CloneArmy generates:\n- A sorted BAM file with alignments\n- A CSV file containing haplotype information:\n  - Sequence\n  - Read count\n  - Frequency\n  - Number of mutations\n- Console output with rich fo"], "modules": [{"name": "cloneArmy", "documentation": ["CloneArmy: A tool for analyzing haplotypes from Illumina paired-end amplicon sequencing."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cloneArmy.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloneArmy.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cloneArmy.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "cloneArmy.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "cloneArmy.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "cloneArmy.AmpliconProcessor", "xref": {"fqname": "cloneArmy.processor.AmpliconProcessor", "project": null}}, {"name": "cloneArmy.process_samples", "xref": {"fqname": "cloneArmy.utils.process_samples", "project": null}}, {"name": "cloneArmy.summarize_results", "xref": {"fqname": "cloneArmy.utils.summarize_results", "project": null}}, {"name": "cloneArmy.validate_input", "xref": {"fqname": "cloneArmy.utils.validate_input", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "cloneArmy.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "cloneArmy.utils.process_samples", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fastq_dir", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "reference", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "output_dir", "type": {"name": "Union", 